B.Nc=s([B.LP,B.LM,B.Lu],t.EF)
B.Lo=new A.f_(8,"Basic Risk Factors","Unit 8: Things that can raise risk","NCI Dictionary of Cancer Terms \ufffd risk factor\nNCI Dictionary of Cancer Terms \ufffd smoking\nMedlinePlus \ufffd Family History","https://www.cancer.gov/publications/dictionaries/cancer-terms/def/risk-factor\nhttps://www.cancer.gov/publications/dictionaries/cancer-terms/def/smoking\nhttps://medlineplus.gov/familyhistory.html",u.u,"A risk factor is something that raises the chance of getting a disease. A risk factor does not guarantee that someone will get sick, but it can make the chance higher. Smoking is one example of a risk factor for many diseases. Diet, age, and family history can matter too. Learning about risk factors is part of learning about health, because risk is about chances and patterns, not certainty.","The last beginner unit explains risk factors using everyday words.",B.MK,B.Nc)
