B.KM=new A.iP("Move Around","This is the arena. Move with WASD, arrow keys, or the on-screen joystick. Staying mobile is your main defense.","Try circling the arena for a few seconds.")
B.KP=new A.iP("Dash To Reposition","Dash with Space or the DASH button. Use it to slip through gaps, dodge boss lanes, or escape when enemies surround you.","Dash once, then keep moving.")
B.KR=new A.iP("Mini-Weapons Attack For You","Your tutorial run starts with Turret equipped. Mini-weapons fire automatically, so your job is positioning and choosing upgrades.","Let the turret clear nearby enemies while you kite.")
B.KT=new A.iP("Samples Are XP","Enemies drop green samples. Pick them up to fill the sample bar at the top-left and earn one in-wave upgrade choice.","Collect samples until the bar fills.")
B.KS=new A.iP("Upgrade Choices","When the sample bar fills, choose a mini-weapon upgrade. Upgrades should change how weapons behave, not just raise numbers.","Pick an upgrade if the choice popup appears.")
B.KN=new A.iP("Read The HUD","The compact HUD shows lives, round timer, sample progress, and boss health. Use it to know when to play safe.","Watch the top-left during the wave.")
B.KO=new A.iP("Cleanup And Lessons","When a wave ends, samples flicker during cleanup. Normal runs then show a lesson, quiz, and build draft.","Stay alive until cleanup begins.")
B.KQ=new A.iP("Boss Gates","Every third normal round becomes a boss gate. Boss tips appear before the fight, and clearing the boss earns a premium reward.","Press Finish when you are ready to return to the home page.")
B.OY=s([B.KM,B.KP,B.KR,B.KT,B.KS,B.KN,B.KO,B.KQ],A.ag("t<iP>"))
B.HJ=new A.eV("yes_samples","Yes, add samples","Best Survivor-style fit. Gives each round momentum and real-time build decisions without removing lessons.")
B.HN=new A.eV("small_orbs_only","Yes, but light-touch","Adds a small amount of in-round growth, but keeps most power in the round-end shop.")
B.HH=new A.eV("no_samples","No, keep current structure","Safer scope, but combat may stay less dynamic because progression still happens almost entirely after a round ends.")
B.OB=s([B.HJ,B.HN,B.HH],t.ST)
B.HU=new A.oG("mid_round_progression","Question 1","To make combat feel more like Vampire Survivors, should each round have its own in-combat XP or sample meter that grants level-up choices before the lesson screen?","The current game only spikes in power between rounds. That means each combat segment can feel flat even when the build system is good.","yes_samples","Recommended: yes. Keep coins for the education/shop loop, but add a separate in-round XP or sample meter so every round has 2 to 4 exciting power spikes.",B.OB)
B.HR=new A.eV("density_plus_elites","Density + elites","Large swarms with occasional high-value threats. Strongest fit for a Vampire Survivors-like feel.")
B.HP=new A.eV("mostly_elites","Mostly elites","More tactical and readable, but less horde-spectacle.")
B.HK=new A.eV("objective_moments","Objective moments","Adds variety with escort, zone, or survival tasks, but moves farther from the pure Survivor formula.")
B.P9=s([B.HR,B.HP,B.HK],t.ST)
B.HT=new A.oG("round_density","Question 2","Once in-round progression exists, what should be the main source of entertainment inside a wave: huge enemy density, dangerous elites, or objective-style moments?","This decides whether the game feels like a horde survival lawnmower, a tactical arena with priority targets, or a more event-driven survival game.","density_plus_elites","Recommended: huge density plus occasional elites. That is the closest match to Survivor-style excitement while still fitting the existing auto-fire and boss framework.",B.P9)
B.HM=new A.eV("mostly_weapon_growth","Mostly weapon growth","Best for synergy, clarity, and satisfying \u201cmy build is coming online\u201d moments.")
B.HI=new A.eV("mostly_passives","Mostly passives","Cleaner to balance, but less immediately exciting than visible weapon changes.")
B.HQ=new A.eV("temporary_spikes","Temporary spikes","Very flashy, but can make runs feel swingy instead of steadily stronger.")
B.Nr=s([B.HM,B.HI,B.HQ],t.ST)
B.HS=new A.oG("power_choice_style","Question 3","When the player levels up during combat, should the choices mostly improve existing weapons, add new passive effects, or introduce temporary power spikes?","This determines whether the game becomes a build-crafting run, a spectacle engine, or a burst-heavy arcade game.","mostly_weapon_growth","Recommended: mostly improve existing weapons plus a few passives. It builds clear synergies and keeps the player learning one run at a time.",B.Nr)
B.HL=new A.eV("performance_first","Performance first","Lets us safely raise enemy counts and effect density after the audit.")
B.HO=new A.eV("readability_first","Readability first","Safer refactor path, but delays the big horde-feel upgrades.")
B.HG=new A.eV("balanced_pass","Balanced pass","Split effort between cleanup and performance, but progress on both will be slower.")
B.NP=s([B.HL,B.HO,B.HG],t.ST)
B.HV=new A.oG("optimization_priority","Question 4","While we make the game more entertaining, should the first technical optimization pass focus on performance during dense waves or on readability and bug-proofing first?","The code currently does repeated full-scene scans for collisions, target search, and area damage. That is fine now, but it will start to matter once enemy counts climb.","performance_first","Recommended: performance during dense waves first. Survivor-style fun depends on supporting more enemies, more effects, and more projectiles without the game getting mushy.",B.NP)
B.P0=s([B.HU,B.HT,B.HS,B.HV],A.ag("t<oG>"))
